President Muhammadu Buhari on Sunday stated that Vice President Professor Yemi Osinbajo is in charge of the country while he is away on a medical trip in the United Kingdom. Buhari disclosed this while speaking to reporters in Abuja at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, expressing that the administration will be well taken care of in the capable hands of the Vice President. “Well, I cannot claim to be doing the work alone. The government is fully represented; the vice president is there; constitutionally when I’m away, he’s in charge,” he said. Crack In CECPC Widens Ahead Of  APC Convention Oloyede Flays Discrimination Against Girl-Child Recall that the President was supposed to travel to London after attending the 50th Anniversary of the UN Environmental Programme in Nairobi, Kenya, however, in he returned to Abuja on Friday.